03:36.915 --> 03:39.108
[music playing]

04:28.876 --> 04:31.773
[Footsteps]

04:38.251 --> 04:41.886
I'm so sorry, Jack.

04:41.887 --> 04:44.099
This is bull, Hayley.

04:44.100 --> 04:46.088
Crescent tradition
says you have a funeral

04:46.089 --> 04:49.127
at dawn, and no one is here.

04:49.650 --> 04:51.796
That loyalty...

04:51.797 --> 04:54.604
Loyalty is gone.

04:56.630 --> 04:59.502
We're standing around
moping over Ollie's body

04:59.503 --> 05:01.616
when there's a war to be fought.

05:01.617 --> 05:04.619
I understand that
you have to grieve, Jack.

05:04.620 --> 05:06.076
You waited for me.

05:06.077 --> 05:08.450
So I'll do the same for you,

05:08.451 --> 05:10.787
but our people need their Alpha.

05:20.968 --> 05:23.536
[Sniffles]

05:23.537 --> 05:25.890
Marcel: Where's your Alpha?

05:25.891 --> 05:27.007
Unavailable.

05:27.008 --> 05:28.575
So you brought Junior varsity?

05:28.576 --> 05:29.942
I'm getting a little
tired of you

05:29.943 --> 05:32.564
using my place as a den
for wayward wolves.

05:32.565 --> 05:34.544
Oh, it's just that we
were going to take down

05:34.545 --> 05:36.234
Finn Mikaelson today,
and considering

05:36.235 --> 05:38.749
how he treated your vampires,
I assumed that you

05:38.750 --> 05:41.988
would want in on the bloodbath.

05:41.989 --> 05:44.447
I'm listening.

05:44.448 --> 05:47.623
Well, it's not gonna be easy.

05:47.624 --> 05:50.290
He's surrounded by a pack
of juiced-up wolves.

05:50.291 --> 05:51.660
He doesn't have a weakness.

05:51.661 --> 05:52.928
He does, actually,

05:52.929 --> 05:55.131
and I have her on speed dial.

05:55.132 --> 05:56.700
He's got a thing for Cami.

05:56.701 --> 05:59.257
Klaus would go ballistic if
we get Cami involved in this.

05:59.258 --> 06:01.775
Klaus ain't here,
and Cami, well,

06:01.776 --> 06:03.677
she's got this thing
about people telling her

06:03.678 --> 06:06.147
what she can and can't do.

06:06.148 --> 06:10.055
Trust you, of all
people, understand.

06:11.386 --> 06:13.355
He hasn't called.

06:13.356 --> 06:15.122
He thinks he's protecting me,

06:15.123 --> 06:18.490
but I don't think
I want to be protected.

06:18.491 --> 06:19.758
Truth be told, I don't think

06:19.759 --> 06:22.427
I want to be around him
anymore at all.

06:22.428 --> 06:26.237
Well, that's a nice
piece of progress.

06:29.914 --> 06:31.493
What's on your mind?

06:31.966 --> 06:36.001
I was wondering. I...

06:36.002 --> 06:39.839
I know this is, like,
horribly unprofessional,

06:39.840 --> 06:45.715
but I was hoping I could
genew advisor.

06:49.545 --> 06:52.015
You aren't finding our
sessions productive?

06:52.016 --> 06:54.479
No. No.
That's not it.

06:54.480 --> 06:55.851
They've been great.

06:55.852 --> 06:58.353
You're really getting
to know me.

06:58.354 --> 07:01.820
I just...

07:01.821 --> 07:04.150
I want to get to know you, too.

07:08.289 --> 07:10.698
Uh...

07:12.025 --> 07:14.363
Right. Yes. Heh.

07:14.364 --> 07:17.330
Mortifyingly unprofessional.
I'm gonna go.

07:19.835 --> 07:23.586
Uh, Camile...

07:28.389 --> 07:30.468
Do you enjoy jazz?

07:38.149 --> 07:42.444
[Chanting]

07:42.445 --> 07:45.682
[Glass cracking]

07:54.061 --> 07:55.452
Still at it?

07:55.931 --> 07:57.620
[Glass shatters]

07:59.267 --> 08:01.104
I'm trying to repair
the damage that you did

08:01.105 --> 08:02.380
to my delinking spell.

08:02.381 --> 08:04.942
Oh.

08:04.943 --> 08:07.244
The only reason I'm still
shacked up in this dump motel

08:07.803 --> 08:10.115
with you is for your freaky
witch encyclopedia brain.

08:10.116 --> 08:13.083
Ok. Well, here's
a magical secret

08:13.084 --> 08:16.519
from the ancient legends
of the Romani psychics...

08:16.520 --> 08:18.687
Sleep, Davina.

08:18.688 --> 08:20.482
You've been awake for days.

08:20.483 --> 08:21.660
Kind of hard to rest

08:21.661 --> 08:23.362
with a 1,000-year-old
psycho in the next bed.

08:23.363 --> 08:24.428
When you say that, I sound

08:24.429 --> 08:25.696
like a bit of a creeper.

08:25.697 --> 08:26.764
Can you just stop?

08:26.765 --> 08:27.999
Stop what, darling.

08:28.000 --> 08:29.433
Calling me darling
and trying to be funny

08:29.434 --> 08:32.869
and... all of that.

08:32.870 --> 08:35.767
Oh, well, most girls
like this, but then

08:35.768 --> 08:37.803
you're not like most
girls, are you?

08:37.804 --> 08:41.336
What I'd like is for you
to just stop messing around.

08:41.337 --> 08:42.856
Ok, Davina.
All right.

08:43.378 --> 08:46.090
I have been trying to charm you,

08:46.091 --> 08:47.842
and your resistance
is as impressive

08:47.843 --> 08:50.752
as it is baffling,
but there are things

08:50.753 --> 08:53.014
that we can do, big things.

08:53.015 --> 08:55.888
I can't share
my secrets with you

08:55.889 --> 08:58.061
unless we trust each other.

08:58.062 --> 09:00.486
I don't care about
your secrets, Kaleb...

09:00.487 --> 09:03.399
Kol. I don't even
know what to call you.

09:03.400 --> 09:05.557
Kol Mikaelson,

09:05.558 --> 09:07.024
and if you want
to take down Klaus

09:07.025 --> 09:09.124
without your
friends dying, well,

09:09.125 --> 09:11.094
then you'd be a fool
not to listen to me.

09:11.095 --> 09:13.321
Uh! Ooh...

09:14.286 --> 09:16.409
Uh...

09:16.410 --> 09:17.998
What's happening?

09:17.999 --> 09:20.632
That's mother dearest
calling me home.

09:20.633 --> 09:24.791
[Panting]

09:26.137 --> 09:27.807
Well, you always did know how

09:27.808 --> 09:30.312
to leave a message, mother.

09:30.313 --> 09:33.805
If only all my sons were
as respectful as you are.

09:33.806 --> 09:35.890
Kol will return home soon.

09:35.891 --> 09:37.792
Elijah will wake from
his slumber believing

09:37.793 --> 09:39.929
the only way to salvage
his humanity

09:39.930 --> 09:43.231
is to rejoin our family,
which is why

09:43.232 --> 09:46.276
it is time you bring Camile in.

09:46.277 --> 09:48.987
Here. I've spelled this
to subdue her

09:48.988 --> 09:51.107
without causing bodily harm.

09:51.108 --> 09:52.615
I thought we had more time.

09:52.616 --> 09:54.276
We don't.

09:54.277 --> 09:56.111
Once Klaus has been
duly influenced

09:56.112 --> 09:59.455
by his father, we will
need to act quickly.

09:59.456 --> 10:02.287
No. There's no need for this.

10:05.546 --> 10:08.543
I can bring her in without it.

10:31.521 --> 10:34.027
Stop following me.

10:43.514 --> 10:44.780
I have no intention of
taking Esther's bargain

10:44.781 --> 10:46.502
and no desire to be
remade a mortal being.

10:46.503 --> 10:47.714
Now kindly piss off.

10:47.715 --> 10:50.960
I'm in a hurry to help
my real family.

10:52.019 --> 10:54.761
You seek the Marelok orchid.

10:54.762 --> 10:56.471
How did you know that?

10:56.472 --> 10:58.890
I saw you carry Elijah
home last night.

10:58.891 --> 11:00.833
Who do you think used
to find the orchid

11:00.834 --> 11:03.307
for your mother to put
Mikael to sleep?

11:03.308 --> 11:07.226
Without my help, you
could search forever.

11:10.944 --> 11:13.708
My mother brought you
back from the dead.

11:13.709 --> 11:15.812
My sense of strategy
tells me it wasn't

11:15.813 --> 11:18.449
to play a father-son
game of hide-and-seek.

11:18.450 --> 11:20.386
You can storm off in a fit

11:20.387 --> 11:22.353
of stubbornness if you like,

11:22.354 --> 11:26.120
but I suggest you do
so toward the west.

11:32.049 --> 11:35.026
[Classical music playing]

11:41.517 --> 11:44.207
[Blues music playing]

11:46.012 --> 11:47.747
[Music stops]

11:47.748 --> 11:49.748
Ha ha!

11:49.749 --> 11:51.515
You have any fun
with magic, or is it all

11:51.516 --> 11:54.181
just angst and child
sacrifice with you lot?

11:54.182 --> 11:55.416
You were a witch before you were

11:55.417 --> 11:57.185
a vampire, right?
Yeah.

11:57.186 --> 12:00.054
None of my siblings have
tapped into their power,

12:00.055 --> 12:02.989
little bit of a child prodigy.

12:02.990 --> 12:05.524
I loved it.
I loved the power.

12:05.525 --> 12:08.063
I loved the rush,

12:08.064 --> 12:11.045
and then when we turned,
I lost it all,

12:11.046 --> 12:12.867
went through a bit
of a dark period.

12:12.868 --> 12:14.735
1,000 years?
Yeah.

12:14.736 --> 12:16.974
Well, I'm a thrill seeker.

12:16.975 --> 12:18.409
Couldn't get that
from magic anymore,

12:18.410 --> 12:21.013
so I looked elsewhere.

12:21.014 --> 12:22.598
Murder, mayhem.

12:22.599 --> 12:24.847
Youthful misadventures.

12:24.848 --> 12:27.684
I actually spent quite
a lot of time with witches,

12:27.685 --> 12:30.521
learning from them,
teaching them,

12:30.522 --> 12:33.257
trying to get back what
my mother stole from me.

12:33.258 --> 12:36.058
Is that why she brought
you back as a witch?

12:36.059 --> 12:38.094
She felt like this body

12:38.095 --> 12:41.297
would be the best
for the task at hand...

12:41.298 --> 12:44.737
Spying on the
prettiest witch in town.

12:44.738 --> 12:46.507
Can't believe your
mom sent you here

12:46.508 --> 12:48.332
to flirt with me.

12:48.333 --> 12:51.378
No, no. She sent me
to follow you.

12:51.379 --> 12:55.668
The flirting bit was me.

12:56.818 --> 13:00.256
[Classical music playing]

13:03.727 --> 13:06.768
Cami said Vincent wants to
meet at preservation hall,

13:06.769 --> 13:08.130
but he won't be unprotected.

13:08.131 --> 13:10.998
There'll be wolves
positioned here and here.

13:11.527 --> 13:13.316
Can we keep this alley open?

13:13.317 --> 13:14.671
Great.
We'll wait there

13:14.672 --> 13:16.402
and rip Vincent's head off.

13:16.403 --> 13:17.820
Nah. He'll body jump.

13:17.821 --> 13:19.405
His head stays on.

13:19.406 --> 13:21.617
He'll have a hard time
answering our questions

13:21.618 --> 13:23.659
without it.

13:23.660 --> 13:28.414
Sweet. It's a big box
of dusty, old junk. We're saved.

13:28.415 --> 13:30.560
They're dark objects
my uncle left for me.

13:30.561 --> 13:32.596
I've been cataloging them
according to Kieran's notes.

13:32.597 --> 13:34.297
As far as I can tell,
these can be used

13:34.298 --> 13:36.399
against witches specifically.

13:36.400 --> 13:38.424
Kinky.

13:38.425 --> 13:40.305
I remember these.
What?

13:40.306 --> 13:42.303
100 years ago, the human faction

13:42.304 --> 13:44.138
waged a war
against the voodoo queens.

13:44.139 --> 13:45.809
They had a trader
spell these manacles.

13:45.810 --> 13:47.780
You slap them on a witch,

13:47.781 --> 13:49.818
they can't do magic
as long as they're on.

13:49.819 --> 13:51.421
All right.

13:51.422 --> 13:52.890
Well, we're not gonna get
the handcuffs of doom on him

13:52.891 --> 13:54.391
while he's surrounded
by a werewolf entourage.

13:54.392 --> 13:56.818
We just lure him away.
I can do that.

13:56.819 --> 13:59.767
Cami, if we do this,
you're the bait.

13:59.768 --> 14:03.277
Are you sure you're
ok with that?

14:06.679 --> 14:09.151
Make it look convincing.

14:09.152 --> 14:11.410
The guy is really smart.

14:12.827 --> 14:15.396
Ansel: 1,000 years estranged,

14:15.397 --> 14:17.933
and you choose
to walk in silence.

14:17.934 --> 14:20.129
Surely, you have
questions for me.

14:20.130 --> 14:22.441
Just one.

14:22.442 --> 14:23.842
Is there a way to cure Elijah

14:23.843 --> 14:24.876
without having to listen
to the pointless

14:24.877 --> 14:27.813
ramblings of an old man?

14:27.814 --> 14:30.476
I'm afraid the price
of my expertise

14:30.477 --> 14:33.354
is conversation.

14:33.355 --> 14:35.059
You know, I used
to tell myself that

14:35.060 --> 14:38.192
my real father must have
had no idea I existed.

14:38.193 --> 14:41.130
Otherwise, he'd never leave
me to suffer under Mikael.

14:41.131 --> 14:43.001
Esther forbade me
from seeing you.

14:43.002 --> 14:44.737
So I waited, knowing
that one day,

14:44.738 --> 14:46.073
you would trigger your curse

14:46.074 --> 14:49.031
and need your real father...

14:50.577 --> 14:53.446
But when that happened,
Mikael found me first.

14:54.916 --> 14:56.794
I fought him for you.
Yes.

14:56.795 --> 14:59.317
Well, your grand declaration
is just a few years too late.

14:59.318 --> 15:00.552
Now, you joke, but I know you've

15:00.553 --> 15:02.688
always felt a void in your life.

15:02.689 --> 15:04.623
I've watched you from
beyond for centuries.

15:04.624 --> 15:06.624
You've traveled all
corners of the world,

15:06.625 --> 15:08.426
seen monuments erected,
feasted on the blood

15:08.427 --> 15:10.363
of history's most
extraordinary men,

15:10.364 --> 15:12.930
but you've never
found true peace.

15:15.765 --> 15:17.432
The only moments of joy
in your life,

15:17.433 --> 15:22.000
however fleeting, have
been simple pleasures...

15:22.001 --> 15:24.906
As you climbed the Himalayas,

15:24.907 --> 15:27.308
as you tended to your horses,

15:27.309 --> 15:29.144
quiet days teaching
that boy Shakespeare.

15:29.145 --> 15:31.280
Stop.
I watched you paint.

15:31.281 --> 15:33.548
I watched you feel your
unborn daughter's kick.

15:34.082 --> 15:36.751
I said stop.

15:36.752 --> 15:39.757
A millennium of observing me,

15:39.758 --> 15:42.715
were your eyes closed as
I slaughtered whole villages,

15:42.716 --> 15:44.963
fed my way through
thousands of innocents?

15:44.964 --> 15:46.636
Because...
Let's face it...

15:46.637 --> 15:49.258
I have a tendency
to play with my food.

15:54.208 --> 15:58.893
Have I made you proud, father?

16:10.827 --> 16:13.537
Remind me to teach you
how to send a text message.

16:13.538 --> 16:16.499
You were told to get the
white oak stake days ago.

16:16.500 --> 16:18.793
We need it now,

16:18.794 --> 16:21.295
seeing as your father has risen.

16:21.296 --> 16:24.911
Mikael?

16:24.912 --> 16:27.298
Back from the dead?
Enough.

16:27.299 --> 16:29.148
You kept it from me.

16:29.149 --> 16:30.930
Why, because of Davina Claire?

16:30.931 --> 16:32.251
To protect your plan.

16:32.252 --> 16:33.553
She's never gonna trust me
if she thinks I'm just

16:33.554 --> 16:35.768
a flying monkey
to the wicked witch.

16:35.769 --> 16:37.848
I've got it handled, mother.

16:49.950 --> 16:52.076
I want that stake,
and I don't care

16:52.077 --> 16:54.740
what you have to do to get it.

17:22.858 --> 17:26.277
Vervain.
It's everywhere.

17:26.278 --> 17:28.607
My relentless mother
has set a trap.

17:30.328 --> 17:32.763
I'll retrieve
the Marelok for you.

17:33.285 --> 17:35.299
At what cost?

17:35.300 --> 17:37.200
Why don't you use
your vampire abilities

17:37.201 --> 17:38.998
to end your doubts?

17:38.999 --> 17:40.405
Search my mind.

17:40.406 --> 17:42.442
You'll see I'm not
allied with your mother.

17:42.443 --> 17:44.680
I have absolutely no interest

17:44.681 --> 17:47.757
in the inner workings
of your brain.

17:47.758 --> 17:49.383
I'm surprised at your cowardice.

17:49.384 --> 17:52.011
While you stand here
in fear of me,

17:52.012 --> 17:54.300
your brother suffers further.

17:57.129 --> 18:00.731
Gather the orchids.

18:11.948 --> 18:14.316
What'd your mother
want from you?

18:14.317 --> 18:16.385
She wants me to take that stake

18:16.386 --> 18:18.751
out of your bag, give it to her

18:18.752 --> 18:20.652
so that you can't kill Klaus

18:20.653 --> 18:22.722
before she gets her
big, happy family.

18:22.723 --> 18:24.376
Is that why you called me here?

18:24.377 --> 18:26.003
I'm not my mother's puppet.

18:26.004 --> 18:29.048
I want something
different entirely.

18:29.049 --> 18:33.385
I want your blood.
Relax, luv.

18:33.386 --> 18:37.413
I'm not gonna take it.
I'm asking you nicely.

18:37.414 --> 18:38.515
Sure. I'll just bleed for you

18:38.516 --> 18:41.617
without any explanation at all.

18:41.618 --> 18:44.352
About 100 years ago,

18:44.353 --> 18:47.149
this tomb used to be
my playhouse.

18:47.150 --> 18:48.759
The witches I used to run with,

18:48.760 --> 18:51.697
they used to make all
kinds of magic in here,

18:51.698 --> 18:54.430
that is, until I pissed
the prettiest one off,

18:54.431 --> 18:57.576
as I tend to do, and,
well, she locked me out.

18:57.577 --> 18:59.370
So why do you need my blood?

18:59.371 --> 19:03.499
Her name was Mary-Alice Claire.

19:03.500 --> 19:08.053
Only a Claire witch
can open this tomb.

19:23.472 --> 19:26.409
Where'd you get all this stuff?

19:26.410 --> 19:28.411
Well, I was a vampire.

19:28.412 --> 19:31.193
I could get anything I wanted,

19:31.194 --> 19:33.154
but I couldn't
practice witchcraft.

19:33.155 --> 19:35.456
So I charmed some witches,
and I taught them

19:35.457 --> 19:37.762
a new kind of magic that
I learned in Arabia

19:37.763 --> 19:40.563
called Kemiya.

19:40.564 --> 19:43.898
We made items that
allowed me to use magic

19:43.899 --> 19:46.250
without doing magic.

19:46.251 --> 19:48.438
You taught them how
to make dark objects.

19:48.439 --> 19:50.908
Yeah, and for a time,

19:51.426 --> 19:53.110
they were scattered
all around the city.

19:53.111 --> 19:54.410
I can't for the life
of me find out

19:54.411 --> 19:57.094
where they are now, but...

19:57.095 --> 19:58.929
I've got the one that matters.

19:58.930 --> 20:00.055
What is it?

20:00.056 --> 20:01.852
It's not about what it is.

20:01.853 --> 20:04.254
It's about what it could be.

20:04.255 --> 20:06.809
You want to take
down Klaus, right?

20:06.810 --> 20:10.430
I've wanted one
thing for years...

20:10.431 --> 20:13.444
To drive a dagger into his heart

20:13.445 --> 20:16.702
like he's done to me
so many times.

20:16.703 --> 20:19.908
Those daggers
don't work on Klaus.

20:19.909 --> 20:22.324
Smart girl.

20:22.325 --> 20:26.283
With a little practice
and some trust,

20:26.284 --> 20:28.521
we'll fix it so this one will.

20:28.522 --> 20:30.521
We'll put him in a box.

20:30.522 --> 20:32.055
Seeing as he won't
be entirely dead,

20:32.056 --> 20:35.257
your friends will be safe.

20:35.258 --> 20:37.343
So what do you say?

20:37.344 --> 20:39.845
[Dixieland jazz music playing]

20:39.846 --> 20:42.468
[Bell rings]

20:57.739 --> 21:00.931
Thank you.
This is amazing.

21:00.932 --> 21:02.834
I developed an appreciation

21:02.835 --> 21:04.337
for the music when I moved here.

21:04.338 --> 21:06.450
I never had a taste
for it before.

21:07.916 --> 21:09.380
I see you're still developing

21:09.381 --> 21:11.850
your taste for beer.

21:11.851 --> 21:13.553
My mom said beer
wasn't ladylike.

21:13.554 --> 21:16.006
So I learned to love it
as an act of rebellion.

21:16.007 --> 21:17.094
What about you?

21:17.095 --> 21:19.532
Snobby mom, distant dad?
Let's go.

21:19.533 --> 21:22.263
Well, my mother and
I are quite close.

21:22.264 --> 21:24.067
She made so many
sacrifices for us,

21:24.068 --> 21:27.268
now anything she asks seem
negligible in comparison.

21:27.269 --> 21:28.372
[Cell phone rings]

21:28.373 --> 21:31.511
Oh. Hold on. So sorry.
Can you hold this?

21:34.115 --> 21:36.519
Oh, I have to take this.

21:36.520 --> 21:37.888
A friend is covering my shift.

21:37.889 --> 21:41.128
I'll be right back.
I'm so sorry.

22:01.386 --> 22:04.138
Cami: Aah! Aah! Aah!

22:04.139 --> 22:06.932
Aah! Aah!

22:06.933 --> 22:08.637
Hey!

22:18.403 --> 22:19.508
[Hayley whistles]

22:36.529 --> 22:39.695
Klaus: I've always seen a blade
to have a very different use.

22:39.696 --> 22:41.898
Mikael taught you
to kill, Klaus,

22:41.899 --> 22:44.049
but you were born to create.

22:44.050 --> 22:47.428
Power lies in embracing
your true nature.

22:47.429 --> 22:50.607
You think I should accept
my mother's offer,

22:50.608 --> 22:52.910
sacrifice my vampirism.

22:52.911 --> 22:55.782
Then what, become a florist?

22:55.783 --> 22:57.775
[Chuckles]

22:57.776 --> 23:00.319
You wouldn't be
sacrificing anything.

23:00.320 --> 23:01.886
As a wolf, you could be king

23:01.887 --> 23:04.721
to an entire species.

23:05.241 --> 23:07.488
You would feel true peace.

23:09.662 --> 23:12.910
You would be a better father.

23:16.673 --> 23:20.576
I am no longer a father.

23:22.967 --> 23:24.377
In our animal form,

23:24.378 --> 23:26.781
we feel everything more acutely.

23:26.782 --> 23:28.519
When you were a boy,
after each full moon,

23:28.520 --> 23:30.256
I would wake closer
to your village,

23:30.257 --> 23:33.256
having been drawn
to you in the night.

23:33.770 --> 23:36.692
Since I've been back,
each month when I turn,

23:36.693 --> 23:40.646
I wake further from New Orleans.

23:42.437 --> 23:45.025
I know the call of
my own blood, Klaus.

23:49.974 --> 23:53.492
I know your child
is still alive.

24:01.817 --> 24:05.444
It was a wolf bite.
Who broke rank?

24:05.510 --> 24:07.469
I'll knock some heads
together and find out.

24:07.470 --> 24:10.222
I'll know where
Camile is shortly.

24:10.223 --> 24:12.292
You'll meet me there.

24:12.293 --> 24:13.627
Come alone

24:13.628 --> 24:16.227
because your wolves
can't be trusted.

24:16.228 --> 24:17.641
[Beep]

24:19.062 --> 24:20.965
[Beep]

24:20.966 --> 24:22.734
Well, he bought it.

24:22.735 --> 24:24.653
His locator spell
will bring him here

24:24.654 --> 24:26.024
without the bodyguards.

24:28.658 --> 24:30.038
I always thought
having a woman's mouth

24:30.039 --> 24:31.702
on my neck would be more erotic.

24:31.703 --> 24:33.312
You'll heal fast.

24:33.313 --> 24:36.285
Let's get all these
lights off. Here.

24:44.522 --> 24:46.792
We're so going to hell for this.

24:46.793 --> 24:50.158
Ha ha! Yeah.
You get used to it.

24:50.159 --> 24:53.628
Hey, I know this probably
isn't your ideal friday night.

24:54.184 --> 24:56.368
I'm sure you'd rather be,
like, doing pushups

24:56.369 --> 25:00.138
or drinking beers with
your bros or whatever.

25:00.139 --> 25:03.975
Eh, it's not so bad.

25:05.079 --> 25:06.914
Cami: Ok. Tell me
the plan one more time.

25:06.915 --> 25:08.548
Aiden is gonna get
Vincent to the altar,

25:08.549 --> 25:09.949
and then I'm gonna jump him.

25:09.950 --> 25:11.216
He's powerful, though,
so we only have

25:11.217 --> 25:13.317
a few seconds to get
the shackles on him.

25:13.786 --> 25:14.723
Where's Marcel?

25:14.724 --> 25:16.326
He's looking for Davina.

25:16.327 --> 25:18.168
He heard she was back in town.

25:18.169 --> 25:19.428
Overprotective dad stuff.

25:19.429 --> 25:21.295
If you want to call
ripping Kol Mikaelson

25:21.296 --> 25:23.527
into 1,000 little pieces
protective dad stuff,

25:23.528 --> 25:25.714
then, yeah, that's it.

25:25.715 --> 25:28.102
[Chuckles]

25:30.139 --> 25:31.807
[Snap]

25:31.808 --> 25:34.843
[Music playing]

25:38.788 --> 25:41.556
Kaleb: The hunters who forged
The Originals daggers

25:41.557 --> 25:43.257
to take out my family
didn't know that Klaus

25:43.258 --> 25:47.194
was part werewolf
and vulnerable to silver.

25:47.195 --> 25:49.321
Now, it's impossible
to replicate

25:49.322 --> 25:51.615
the spell cast on the dagger...

25:51.616 --> 25:54.309
Trust me, I've tried...
But it's not impossible

25:54.310 --> 25:56.776
to change the dagger itself.

25:56.777 --> 25:58.778
Now, Kemiya allows
witches to destroy

25:58.779 --> 26:00.214
one element to create another,

26:00.215 --> 26:03.790
say, changing silver
to gold, for example.

26:03.791 --> 26:05.826
So you've been hanging out
with me this whole time

26:05.827 --> 26:08.090
because you don't have
enough power on your own.

26:08.091 --> 26:11.268
Oh, Kemiya is about chemistry.

26:11.269 --> 26:13.340
It's about connection,
and after what happened

26:13.341 --> 26:14.774
with the white oak stake,

26:14.775 --> 26:16.909
I don't think you could
deny what we have.

26:16.910 --> 26:19.745
So, here, hold my hand.

26:19.746 --> 26:22.048
That's a giant diamond.

26:22.049 --> 26:23.684
It's a paragon diamond.

26:24.186 --> 26:27.220
They use them to conduct power.

26:27.221 --> 26:29.319
Is the hand holding
really necessary?

26:29.320 --> 26:31.057
I mean, we could make out,

26:31.058 --> 26:34.324
but would that not be
entirely distracting?

26:34.325 --> 26:36.099
[Sighs]

26:36.100 --> 26:38.865
All right.
Follow my lead.

26:43.209 --> 26:44.496
Close your eyes.

26:47.714 --> 26:49.881
[Chanting]

26:49.882 --> 26:52.087
[Both chanting]

27:01.436 --> 27:02.639
Heh.

27:14.324 --> 27:16.017
[Gasps]

27:34.175 --> 27:37.137
To replace the one I broke.

27:37.138 --> 27:39.640
We changed it.

27:39.641 --> 27:41.883
Oh, Davina Claire,

27:41.884 --> 27:43.930
we're gonna change everything.

27:52.528 --> 27:55.530
This will help Elijah.

27:55.531 --> 27:58.158
Ansel...

27:58.159 --> 28:01.576
I'd be lying if I said
your offer wasn't appealing.

28:01.577 --> 28:05.713
I've never known a parent
to be a benevolent force.

28:08.117 --> 28:12.122
I think I would have liked
to have been your son,

28:12.123 --> 28:14.671
but a different path
was chosen for me,

28:14.672 --> 28:17.964
and I have for
the past 1,000 years

28:17.965 --> 28:23.303
been son of Mikael...
Paranoid, vengeful...

28:25.204 --> 28:28.909
And powerful enough
to protect my daughter.

28:28.910 --> 28:30.604
I want to help you defend her.

28:30.605 --> 28:32.818
I believe you,

28:32.819 --> 28:35.646
but love is what Esther twists.

28:35.647 --> 28:37.482
She will take the best
of your intentions,

28:37.483 --> 28:41.196
and she will use them
to get to my little girl.

28:48.694 --> 28:51.097
You waited too long

28:51.098 --> 28:54.459
before you came to rescue me.

28:59.400 --> 29:03.927
I won't make the same
mistake with hope.

29:10.231 --> 29:12.060
No.

29:14.318 --> 29:16.081
No, Klaus.

29:17.418 --> 29:19.317
I know you.

29:22.034 --> 29:25.574
You are not capable of this.

29:27.295 --> 29:29.786
That's the first lie
you've told me.

29:32.378 --> 29:33.665
Uh!

29:51.022 --> 29:53.622
Oh...

30:05.995 --> 30:09.618
It's late.
I should get going.

30:10.554 --> 30:12.089
Suppose you'll be wanting

30:12.090 --> 30:13.457
to get back to Marcel's.

30:13.458 --> 30:14.891
I lied to him about you.

30:14.892 --> 30:16.293
Probably go back to the attic.

30:16.294 --> 30:18.295
Voluntarily returning
to the jail cell

30:18.296 --> 30:20.998
where they locked you up.

30:20.999 --> 30:26.306
You must have been
lonely all that time.

30:26.307 --> 30:30.140
A witch needs a coven,
even if it is just two.

30:30.141 --> 30:32.813
When can we work on the dagger?

30:32.814 --> 30:35.143
Soon. We got some
more work to do

30:35.144 --> 30:38.772
with each other first.

30:41.976 --> 30:45.659
You're gonna like me,
Davina Claire,

30:45.660 --> 30:49.034
and I'm gonna let you
pretend a while

30:49.035 --> 30:51.868
that you don't already.

30:55.024 --> 30:56.992
Well, I staked it out.

30:56.993 --> 30:58.694
Looks like a couple
of Oliver's friends

30:58.695 --> 31:00.674
wanting to avenge his death.

31:00.675 --> 31:02.217
Where's Cami?

31:02.218 --> 31:03.904
She's tied up near the altar.

31:03.970 --> 31:06.096
Hey, you know what?
You beeline for her.

31:06.097 --> 31:08.141
I'll handle the rest
of them, all right?

31:08.142 --> 31:10.639
Aiden, your brother

31:10.640 --> 31:13.180
was among the recruits
that Oliver rescued.

31:13.181 --> 31:16.248
Was he not?

31:29.662 --> 31:32.098
[Thunder]

31:35.293 --> 31:37.571
Oh, no.

31:37.572 --> 31:39.207
[Crack]

31:40.464 --> 31:43.943
Camile! Camile!

31:46.716 --> 31:48.384
First, I'm gonna kick your ass,

31:48.385 --> 31:49.825
and then I'm gonna
take my pack back.

31:50.311 --> 31:51.151
Your pack?

31:51.152 --> 31:52.653
Last I checked, your pack

31:52.654 --> 31:54.223
was blindly following me.

31:54.224 --> 31:56.021
Want to talk about following?

31:56.022 --> 31:58.232
How do your mother's
boots taste, huh?

31:59.401 --> 32:03.269
Ha! What have you
done with Cami?

32:03.270 --> 32:04.870
Oh!

32:04.871 --> 32:07.237
Hybrids die by losing their head

32:07.238 --> 32:09.039
or their heart.

32:09.040 --> 32:10.877
Given the choice,
I'm gonna take the organ

32:10.878 --> 32:13.380
that got you into this
mess in the first place.

32:13.381 --> 32:17.125
[Chanting]

32:17.126 --> 32:20.332
[Gagging]

32:24.008 --> 32:27.225
Aagh!
Huh!

32:33.059 --> 32:36.014
Aagh!

32:40.406 --> 32:43.104
[Clank clank]

32:46.614 --> 32:48.915
[Sobs]

32:48.916 --> 32:51.740
You would've done the
same thing to me, Finn.

32:51.741 --> 32:54.655
[Chains rattle]

32:54.656 --> 32:57.123
Hey, are you ok?

32:57.124 --> 32:59.459
I'm so sorry I made you wait.

32:59.460 --> 33:03.380
Your timing was
pretty awesome, actually.

33:03.381 --> 33:04.698
Ha ha!

33:09.938 --> 33:12.209
[Elijah panting]

33:25.069 --> 33:27.278
We were innocent once, Elijah.

33:27.279 --> 33:29.529
We were innocent once, Elijah.

33:29.530 --> 33:32.575
[Panting]

33:32.576 --> 33:35.031
[Thunder]

33:36.539 --> 33:38.999
This bloodlust was
forced upon us

33:39.000 --> 33:40.974
by our parents,

33:40.975 --> 33:43.714
turning us from prey
to predator.

33:43.715 --> 33:47.168
[Thunder]

33:54.348 --> 33:57.600
We are the demons
lurking in shadow.

33:57.601 --> 34:00.270
We are the savage villains

34:00.271 --> 34:03.563
in fairy tales told to children,

34:03.564 --> 34:08.817
but not for my child,
not for hope.

34:08.818 --> 34:10.487
In her story,

34:10.489 --> 34:14.907
we are the knights
in shining armor.

34:14.908 --> 34:18.679
Without you by my side,
I don't think I can

34:18.679 --> 34:22.333
survive my own love
for my daughter.

34:22.333 --> 34:26.838
I need you.

34:26.839 --> 34:30.657
I need you, brother.

34:31.222 --> 34:33.096
The monster in me
can only be checked

34:33.097 --> 34:35.054
by the monster in you,

34:35.054 --> 34:37.348
by the monster in you.

34:37.349 --> 34:39.972
Only together can we
defeat our demons

34:40.478 --> 34:42.806
and save our family.

34:47.246 --> 34:50.414
[Thunder]

35:02.458 --> 35:05.580
Hraagh!

35:10.758 --> 35:13.088
[Panting]

35:21.541 --> 35:25.271
[Door opens and closes]

35:25.272 --> 35:27.350
We put Vincent in
the back of Josh's car.

35:27.858 --> 35:29.288
Is Aiden all right?

35:29.289 --> 35:32.792
Mm, some ice and
bourbon, he'll be fine.

35:32.793 --> 35:35.590
How'd you know where to find us?

35:36.158 --> 35:38.829
I spent a lot of time
tracking you when I was a wolf.

35:38.830 --> 35:42.742
Call it animal instinct.

35:43.905 --> 35:46.203
What do you mean?

35:49.208 --> 35:51.947
Oh, Ollie used to
give me so much hell

35:51.948 --> 35:54.347
for waiting on you.

35:54.348 --> 35:56.948
Oh, girls came and went,
but I always knew

35:56.949 --> 35:58.930
someday you'd come.

35:58.931 --> 36:02.058
See, our parents
had been so sure

36:02.059 --> 36:05.770
that you and I could
change things for the better.

36:05.771 --> 36:10.182
Jack, I think the girl
that you were waiting on

36:10.183 --> 36:16.132
was Andrea Labonair,
mythic revolutionary.

36:16.773 --> 36:18.783
You got Hayley Marshall,

36:18.784 --> 36:23.814
a knocked-up tomboy
with a bad attitude.

36:23.815 --> 36:26.350
You got dealt a crappy hand.

36:26.351 --> 36:28.001
[Chuckles]

36:28.002 --> 36:30.155
No. You're right.

36:30.156 --> 36:32.691
You're not the girl
I waited for.

36:35.997 --> 36:38.214
You're better.

36:57.725 --> 37:00.326
What is it?

37:02.028 --> 37:05.121
I spent the day with my father,

37:05.122 --> 37:07.827
my real father.

37:09.137 --> 37:11.673
Esther brought him
back from the dead

37:11.674 --> 37:13.308
believing he could convince me

37:13.309 --> 37:17.943
to renounce vampirism,

37:17.944 --> 37:20.816
and the thought
of what I could be

37:20.817 --> 37:24.224
had I been raised by him...

37:24.225 --> 37:28.811
I'd have been nurtured.

37:28.812 --> 37:32.560
This was his.

37:51.502 --> 37:53.623
He knew about hope...

37:54.429 --> 37:57.545
And I wanted to trust him.

37:57.546 --> 38:02.220
More than anything in
the world, I wanted to,

38:02.221 --> 38:04.074
but...

38:06.543 --> 38:10.603
Uh... I couldn't be sure,

38:10.604 --> 38:12.730
and I would never forgive myself

38:12.731 --> 38:14.186
if something happened to her

38:14.187 --> 38:17.105
because of my selfish
desire for a father.

38:19.460 --> 38:23.365
So I killed him.

38:23.366 --> 38:27.469
Without hesitation,
I killed him.

38:27.470 --> 38:30.575
[Music playing]

38:33.836 --> 38:37.125
You killed him for hope.

38:45.597 --> 38:48.595
Whatever innocence remains

38:48.596 --> 38:53.016
we must protect at any cost.

39:03.198 --> 39:04.777
[Sobs]

39:07.077 --> 39:08.573
[Sobbing]

39:50.207 --> 39:52.533
Yaah! Oh...

40:33.055 --> 40:36.528
Sorry.
We're closed.

40:36.529 --> 40:40.168
That's too bad.

40:40.169 --> 40:44.382
I hear you serve the best
Sazerac in town.

40:44.383 --> 40:47.042
Camile, isn't it?

40:47.553 --> 40:52.557
My sons have taken
quite the liking to you.

40:52.558 --> 40:55.430
[Chanting]

41:00.524 --> 41:03.484
How do you feel?

41:03.485 --> 41:05.960
The worst has passed...

41:07.063 --> 41:09.449
Though I suspect the nightmares

41:09.450 --> 41:11.134
are far from over.

41:11.135 --> 41:12.569
Well, gather your strength.

41:12.570 --> 41:14.071
After the message
I sent mother tonight,

41:14.072 --> 41:17.143
I expect hellfire to rain
down upon us imminently.

41:17.144 --> 41:19.079
We need to make a move
before she strikes.

41:19.080 --> 41:21.982
Marcel: Actually, moves were
made while you were sleeping.

41:21.983 --> 41:23.626
It's good to see you vertical.

41:23.627 --> 41:28.880
Marcel and I each left
a gift for you in the ballroom.

41:30.925 --> 41:33.468
You're welcome.

41:43.908 --> 41:46.569
Kaleb: Kidnapping.

41:46.570 --> 41:50.156
It's a rather unpleasant way
to begin a family reunion.

41:50.157 --> 41:53.905
Well, wait until you see
how we end it.

